Private Grants Alert




 (HOUSING) Community Development Fund
Deadline: Rolling.
The Community Development Financial Institutions Fund makes capital grants, equity investments and awards for technical assistance to community development financial institutions (CDFIs).
More than 1,000 CDFIs serve economically distressed communities by providing credit, capital and financial services that often are unavailable from mainstream financial institutions. CDFIs have loaned and invested billions in the most distressed communities and helped ease homelessness while creating affordable housing.
Even better, the loans and investments have leveraged billions more dollars from the private sector for development activities in low-wealth communities across the nation. Insider's Tip: Since its inception, the fund has made more than $800 million in awards to community development organizations and financial institutions.
Info: www.cdfi.org
